<subsection xml:id="nested-if-statements">
<title>Nested If Statements</title>
<p>Nested if statements allow for multiple conditions to be tested. It is very important that you use curly braces to indicate which parts of an if statement are connected to other parts.</p>
<program language="java">
<code>
if(/* condition1 */) {
    if(/* condition1 */) {
        /* this occurs if both conditions are true */
    } else {
        /* this occurs if condition1 is true, but condition2 is false */
    }
}
else // note that the else does not have () or a condition
{ 
    if(/* condition3 */) {
        /* this occurs if condition1 is false but condition3 is true */
    } else {
        /* this occurs if both conditions are false */
    }
}
</code>
</program>
<p>Note that the else is not always needed.</p>

<p>The following FRQ uses nested logic to determine the final score of a game.</p>
</subsection>

<!-- done -->
